This paper deals with entity typing, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). The proposed model uses embeddings, which are commonly used in NLP and machine learning (ML) in general. The paper also mentions the use of knowledge bases, which are often used in database (DB) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DB (Databases).
